Bank Login and Security Instructions

  • Do Not Share Your Account Number: Never share your account number with anyone, including friends or family. Keep it confidential.
  • Protect Your Personal Information: Avoid disclosing your personal information (such as your name, address, or phone number) in public forums or social media.
  • Keep Your ATM Card Number Confidential: Your ATM card number should be kept secret. Never disclose it to anyone, even if they claim to be from your bank.
  • Safeguard Your PIN: Your ATM PIN is personal and should only be known to you. Do not write it down or share it with anyone.
  • Log Out After Use: Always log out of your banking session when you have finished, especially if using a shared or public computer.
  • Monitor Your Account Activity: Regularly check your account statements and transaction history for any unauthorized or suspicious activity.
  • Be Wary of Phishing Attempts: Do not click on suspicious links or provide personal information in response to unsolicited emails, texts, or calls.
  • Use Secure Networks: Avoid accessing your bank account over public Wi-Fi. Use a secure, private network for online banking.
  • Only Use IFSC Codes from Official Sources: Ensure you use IFSC codes only from trusted sources, such as your bank’s official website or documents.
  • Double-Check Before Transactions: Always double-check the IFSC code when making fund transfers to avoid sending money to the wrong account.
  • Report Lost or Stolen Cards Immediately: If your ATM card is lost or stolen, report it to your bank immediately to prevent unauthorized transactions.
  • Educate Yourself About Online Banking Safety: Stay informed about the latest banking scams and security practices to protect yourself.
